# Production-Ready Checklist

Every completed task must satisfy ALL applicable items before delivery.

## Code

- [ ] Solves the exact requirement — no missing edge cases
- [ ] No debug `console.log`, commented-out code, or temporary hacks
- [ ] TypeScript compiles without errors
- [ ] Lint passes (`npm run lint`)
- [ ] Follows existing project structure and naming
- [ ] English-only code comments (only where non-obvious)

## UI / UX

- [ ] Loading state handled
- [ ] Error state handled with user-friendly message
- [ ] Empty state handled (when list or data-driven)
- [ ] Works on iOS, Android, and Web (or platform scope is documented)
- [ ] Safe area and keyboard handled where relevant
- [ ] Touch targets ≥ 44pt; accessibility labels on interactive elements

## Architecture

- [ ] Reusable pieces extracted to `components/` or `hooks/` when used or likely reused
- [ ] No business logic leaked into primitive UI
- [ ] No hardcoded API URLs — all endpoints in `api/routes/`
- [ ] Service logic in dedicated service file; hook in dedicated hook file
- [ ] Query keys from `QueryKey` enum — no inline strings
- [ ] Realtime channels/events from centralized enums
- [ ] Realtime cache updates tested (created/updated/deleted events)
- [ ] Side effects on shared code documented for the user

## Security (when applicable)

- [ ] No secrets in source code
- [ ] User input validated (Zod when forms are involved)
- [ ] Sensitive data stored in SecureStore, not AsyncStorage

## Delivery Message

When finishing a task, briefly state:

1. What was done
2. Files changed
3. Any risks or side effects for other parts of the app
4. Suggested manual test steps (if non-trivial)
